&lt;div id=&quot;wiki-tab-0-0&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Height:&lt;/strong&gt; 6&#039;2&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;DOB:&lt;/strong&gt; 5/26/1987&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Plays:&lt;/strong&gt; Drums, trumpet (Self Titled), vocals (See You Soon EP), with fire&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Physiology:&lt;/strong&gt; Strained&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;Joshua&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;Lyanna&lt;/span&gt; Veronica Katherine Fitzroy was born to a doomed mother and ill-prepared &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;father&lt;/span&gt; in Staten Island on May 26th, 1987. Infamous for spearheading several of the band&#039;s more notable stunts, Fitzroy&#039;s musical career began at the age of 14, when she realized that screaming got her nothing and drumming got her As.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fitzroy first met her bandmates at her &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;surrogate dad&lt;/span&gt; friend&#039;s suggestion, and remained friends right up to the point where her anger overrode her love.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;wiki-tab-0-1&quot; style=&quot;display:none&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Height:&lt;/strong&gt; 5&#039;3&amp;quot; and above&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;DOB:&lt;/strong&gt; 10/25/1987&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Plays:&lt;/strong&gt; Bass, background vocals (Self Titled, Reefer Infatuation EP, David Cameron Fucked a Dead Pig), vocals (See You Soon EP), with feelings&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Physiology:&lt;/strong&gt; Variable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Isabella Madoka Kawajiri was born to a hyper-conformist mother in South London on October 25th, 1987, &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;escaping&lt;/span&gt; moving with her mother to Austin, Texas in 1990. The unofficial &amp;quot;leader&amp;quot; of House of Spades, Kawajiri&#039;s musical career began at the age of 8, when her &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;step&lt;/span&gt;father bought her her first guitar, stopped at age 13 when her &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;crush&lt;/span&gt;&#039;s boyfriend smashed it apart, and resumed at 14 once she saved enough money to buy a &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;sturdier&lt;/span&gt; bass.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kawajiri first met her bandmates through a couple of &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;mutual&lt;/span&gt; friends, and remained friends right up to the point where her desire for status overrode her sense of caution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;wiki-tab-0-2&quot; style=&quot;display:none&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Height:&lt;/strong&gt; 7&#039;9&amp;quot;/5&#039;6&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;DOB:&lt;/strong&gt; He forgot&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Plays:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead guitar, vocals (David Cameron Fucked a Dead Pig, See You Soon EP), the victim&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Physiology:&lt;/strong&gt; Deceptive&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Jack of Spades was born to King Whale&#039;s Second Consort in a place where time or space didn&#039;t matter all that much. Always the odd one out, Jack&#039;s musical career began in 1956 when a psychological break forced him to realize that people loved a two-legged predator more than a many-legged parasite.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jack first met his bandmates at an audition his &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;lover&lt;/span&gt; friend attended, and remained friends right up to the point where his lust for companionship overrode his empathy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;wiki-tab-0-3&quot; style=&quot;display:none&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Height:&lt;/strong&gt; 5&#039;2&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;DOB:&lt;/strong&gt; 8/29/1988&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Plays:&lt;/strong&gt; Rhythm guitar (sans See You Soon EP), vocals (sans See You Soon EP), herself&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Physiology:&lt;/strong&gt; Crispy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sara Miriam Yarkoni was born to a couple of workaholics in Staten Island on August 29th, 1988 along with her level-headed twin sister Ana. Arguably the glue that kept everything together, Yarkoni&#039;s musical career began at the age of 6, when she took up singing, and branched into guitar at age 19 to keep herself busy following expulsion from Yale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yarkoni first met her bandmates at some thing she went to on impulse, and remained friends right up to the point where her fear overrode her common sense.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

